CONCLUSIONS:

- The accuracy of velocity with th is better than with bf;
- The accuracy of pressure with bf is better than with th; (That is different of the 2d-case)
- The methods f1 and f2 give the same results;
- With the same mesh, the CPU TIME of f2 method is lower than f1 method;
- With the same mesh, the CPU time of bf is lower greater than th;
- The f2 memory storage is very lower than f1;
- The f1 cr memory storage is very greater than f2 ch which is greater than f2 cg;

Finally, the best velocity accuracy method is th2 cg;
         the best pressure accuracy method is bf2 cg.
